      "notes": "The first two parameters influence the amplitude envelope of the generated haptic signal.\n\n<p align=\"center\">\n<img width=\"100%\" src=\"media://assets/amplitudeparameters.png\" />\n\n\n**Gain**\nControls the overall intensity of the haptic output by amplifying or attenuating the amplitude envelope. Increasing the gain results in stronger, more pronounced feedback, while reducing it creates a softer, subtler effect.\n\n/newpage\n**Resolution**\nDetermines the number of breakpoints generated from the audio. A lower value produces a smoother, more simplified envelope. A higher value creates a more detailed envelope with greater fidelity.\n\nExperiment with these parameters and feel how they affect the resulting haptic experience. They are key to shaping both the feel and clarity of the feedback.\n",
