      "notes": "The last set of parameters controls the frequency envelope, which defines how the vibration pitch evolves over time.\n\n<p align=\"center\">\n<img width=\"100%\" src=\"media://assets/frequencyfilters.png\" />\n\n\n**Audio Filter**\nUse this slider to define the frequency range in which the analysis algorithm should focus on when extracting the frequency envelope from the audio.\n\nSource audio often contains high-frequency content that should be heard but not translated into haptic feedback. The Audio Filter allows you to exclude those frequencies, ensuring a cleaner and more relevant haptic signal.\n/newpage\n**Haptic Output**\nThis slider maps the extracted frequency information to the haptic playback range.\n\n**Examples:**\n\n**0–100%** → Wide frequency modulation \n**0–20%**→ only  lower, smoother vibrations\n\n**80–100%** → Emphasizes higher, sharper vibrations\n\nIn the example shown here, we’re working with rising tones in the 100–500 Hz range.",
      "lastUpdate": 1750692747486,
