      "notes": "The ‘Design from Audio’ workflow starts by loading an audio file into the project. \n\nThe design process is divided into two stages: <b>Audio Analysis</b> and <b>Breakpoint Editing</b>.\n\n<b>Audio Analysis</b>\nHaptics Studio automatically analyzes your audio file upon import, generating an initial haptic curve.\nThis provides a strong starting point for creating a haptic clip.\n\n<p align=\"center\">\n<video width=\"100%\" src=\"media://assets/analysis.mp4\" autoplay loop/>\n/newpage\n\nIn most cases, fine-tuning the audio analysis parameters will produce the desired results.\n\nHowever, for more precise control over the haptic output, you can manually adjust the breakpoints in the next stage of the workflow.\n\nYou can influence the resulting haptic output by using the sliders to fine-tune the analysis settings.\n\n/newpage\nSpending time on this step helps ensure a cleaner initial result, making manual editing much easier later on.\n\nLet’s dive into how each parameter affects the analysis and shapes the resulting haptic signal.\n\n",
