      "notes": "Once you're happy with the analysis, you can move on to adjusting breakpoints manually if needed. \n\n<p align=\"center\">\n<video width=\"100%\" src=\"media://assets/breakpointediting.mp4\" autoplay loop/>\n\nSelecting a breakpoint will automatically switch you to the Design tab. You can adjust breakpoints by changing their Time and Amplitude values directly in the value field, or by dragging points in the editor to new positions. \n\n<p align=\"center\"> <img width=\"100%\" src=\"media://assets/adjust.png\"/>\n\n/newpage\nUse the Pen tool to add new points and extend the envelope. Learn more about the Pen tool in the **Freeform Haptics** tutorial.\n\n**Tip:**\nRunning Audio Analysis again will overwrite any manual changes you've made to breakpoints.\n\nTo avoid losing your work, make sure you're satisfied with the analysis settings before starting manual editing.\n\nTo return to the analysis stage, simply switch back to the Audio Analysis tab.\n",
